1. RISK DISCLAIMER
USE TMODLOADER SOFTWARE AT YOUR OWN RISK.
tModLoader is a community created piece of software, which is built upon the base Terraria game to make it possible to introduce changes to the game. Please be aware that anything new or modified in the edited software you may find potentially inaccurate, misleading, dangerous, addictive or unethical. By no means do we support illegal activies or try to incentivize it; our patching system is built in such way that we minimize the publication of decompiled source-code substantially. tModLoader is designed to detect pirated versions and not work with such versions. Any use of pirated sofware is at the user's own discretion and risk. No support will be made available for pirated versions of the game.

YOU ARE HEREBY INFORMED OF THE FOLLOWING (POTENTIAL) RISKS BY USING TMODLOADER'S SOFTWARE OR SERVICES, BUT THEY ARE NOT LIMITED TO:
- Damage of software in the form of corrupted game installs or game files, causing the game to no longer work or no longer work in specific aspects
- Detection of modified client(s) or game files by the content providers (such as Steam, Good Old Games and alike)
- Troubleshooting issues that arise in the game may no longer be prevalent
- Computer damage in any form of hardware damage or other broken pieces that causes the computer to malfunction or break completely
- Distaste in the new state of the game
- Bugs or other software issues that cause tModLoader's software or services to not work correctly

Having that said, tModLoader puts in its best effort to make sure issues like the ones listed arise in such fashion that they can be globally solved for its users and subsequently disappear. However, tModLoader makes no guarantees to make sure this happens or is possible at all.

2. MOD BROWSER DISCLAIMER
THE USAGE OF THE EMBEDDED "MOD BROWSER" SERVICE IN TMODLOADER'S SOFTWARE IS USED AT YOUR OWN DISCRETION.

The Mod Browser is a part of tModLoader's software that allows users to browse mods, read information about them and download and install them with ease. Additionally people that have made mods can upload their work onto the browser using Steam's verification system.

Inherent to the Mod Browser software comes the availability of new information that becomes obtainable by using the piece of software. Not in any shape or form can tModLoader guarantee this information is accurate or without any kind of attempt of subjugation and forms of vulgarity or offense. Any information obtained may be inaccurate, misleading, dangerous, addictive or even unethical.

The Mod Browser software facilitates the ability to upload and download mods. tModLoader reserves the right to monitor and review all use its Mod Browser software to ensure compliance with the terms of this disclaimer.

ANY CONTENT UPLOADED TO THE MOD BROWSER MAY BE REMOVED WITHOUT ANY PRIOR WARNING OR NOTICE, AND ANY USER MAY BE PERMANENTLY DENIED ACCESS FROM THE MOD BROWSER SERVICE WITHOUT THE ABILITY TO APPEAL THIS COURSE OF ACTION. 

In general users will upload mods they worked hard on and would like others to play, with accurate content that means no offense or tries to cause harm in any shape or form. However, any individual or group is perfectly capable of uploading a piece of content that may cause harm to an individual (such as by providing new information as stated earlier in this disclaimer) or software and potentially hardware such as components of their computer. Mods on the mod browser may be subject to contain other harmful additions such as viruses like trojans and keyloggers. TMODLOADER WILL DO ITS BEST TO ENSURE SUCH MODS ARE ADEQUATELY REMOVED FROM THE MOD BROWSER SERVICE, BUT MAINTAINS NO PROMISE TO DO SO AND ACCEPTS NO WARRANTY OR LIABILITY OF ANY KIND FOR ANY DAMAGE CAUSED FROM SUCH CONTENT. ADDITIONALLY TMODLOADER WILL UPHOLD A STANDARD OF REPORTING SUCH MATERIAL AND ITS AUTHOR(S) TO THE STEAM SERVICE THAT IS USED FOR VERIFICATION OF THE MOD BROWSER SERVICE. 

The Mod Browser service only requires Steam authentication to upload new content to it. Any user is free to download any content  made available by the service without any form of authentication. However, tModLoader cannot guarantee the service works correctly at all times. The service may at any given time be taken offline without any prior notice or warning, and be kept unavailable for an unknown period of time. Additionally, tModLoader makes no guarantees to uphold any standards of availability, such as the capability of serving mods to download. The service may be slow or unresponsive depending on the user's geo-location and internet connection. Users of the service are advised to use another service that is not affliated with tModLoader in the case that the Mod Browser service becomes unavailable. tModLoader recommends mod authors to provide additional sources for their mods as well.

Uploaded content to the Mod Browser service preserves no right for special additions, deletions, amendments or other modifications for any specific reason by its author(s) or other users. However, tModLoader holds the right to alter or modify uploaded content in any way desired. This is inclusive to all content being uploaded. 

BY UPLOADING CONTENT TO THE MOD BROWSER SERVICE, YOU INHERENTLY AGREE TO "GIVE POSSESSION OF" WHATEVER CONTENT UPLOADED TO THE SERVICE. HOWEVER, IF AT ANY MOMENT THE SERVICE IS BREACHED AND AS RESULT SUCH CONTENT IS RELEASED FREELY WITH MAL-INTENT, TMODLOADER ACCEPTS NO WARRANTY OR LIABILITY OF ANY KIND FOR THE POTENTIAL DAMAGE OR HARM CAUSED.

IN NO SHAPE OR FORM WILL THE MOD BROWSER ATTEMPT TO CREATE "EXLUSIVITY" FOR CONTENT BEING UPLOADED; ANY USER USING THE SERVICE IS GIVEN ACCESS TO DOWNLOAD ANY UPLOADED CONTENT.

THE SERVICE PROVIDES NO GUARANTEE OF AVAILABILITY FOR ANY UPLOADED CONTENT, OR VALIDITY THEREOF. SUCCESSFULL UPLOAD MESSAGES PROVIDE NO GUARANTEE YOUR CONTENT UPLOADED BECOMES AVAILABLE IN THE SERVICE; THERE IS NO GUARANTEE UPLOADS ARE PROVEN SUCCESSFULL.

BY USING THE SERVICE WITHOUT VERIFICATION THE USER AGREES TO GAIN ACCESS TO POTENTIALLY HARMFUL SOFTWARE OR INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE SERVICE.

Creators of mods preserve the right to remove their uploaded content from the Mod Browser service. However, there is no guarantee that uploaded content has not already propagated through different channels. The uploaded content may exist on different CDNs, including but not limited to: Discord, Github, Dropbox and Imgur. TMODLOADER PRESERVES THE RIGHT TO KEEP UPLOADED CONTENT ON PROPAGATED CHANNELS, EVEN AFTER THE CONTENT WAS REMOVED FROM THE SERVICE; REMOVING UPLOADED CONTENT PROVIDES NO GUARANTEED REMOVAL OF IT IN ITS ENTIRETY. The content will not be removed from users' machines that have downloaded it before it is removed from the service by its creators. NOT IN ANY WAY CAN CONTENT CREATORS FORCE THE REMOVAL OF DOWNLOADED CONTENT THROUGH THIS SERVICE; BY UPLOADING THEIR CONTENT THEY HAVE AUTOMATICALLY GIVEN EXPLICIT PERMISSION FOR THIS CONTENT TO BE PROPAGATED THROUGH DIFFERENT CHANNELS AND END UP ON OTHER PEOPLE'S COMPUTERS.

